com.moniuliuma.fingerprint

Interface Quality

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    QualityImpl

    public interface Quality
    Quality provides image quality calculation algorithms. Currently available: - NIST WSQ algorithm; - Aware WSQ, if licensed instance of Aware WSQ 1000 SDK is available.

    • Method Detail

      • NfiqFid

        int NfiqFid(Fid fid,
            int view_index,
            Quality.QualityAlgorithm quality_alg)
     throws DeviceException
        Calculates NFIQ value of the FID. This function attempts to calculate NFIQ using Aware WSQ library (WSQ1000) or NIST algorithm.
        Parameters:
        fid - - FID to analyze.
        view_index - - The view for which to calculate NFIQ.
        quality_alg - - Calculation algorithm to use.
        Returns:
        NFIQ value.
        Throws:
        DeviceException

      • NfiqRaw

        int NfiqRaw(byte[] data,
            int width,
            int height,
            int dpi,
            int bpp,
            Quality.QualityAlgorithm quality_alg)
     throws DeviceException
        Calculates NFIQ value of the raw image. This function attempts to calculate NFIQ using Aware WSQ library (WSQ1000) or NIST algorithm.
        Parameters:
        data - - Image to compress.
        width - - Width of the image.
        height - - Heght of the image.
        dpi - - Resolution of the image in DPI.
        bpp - - Pixel depth of the image.
        quality_alg - - Calculation algorithm to use.
        Returns:
        NFIQ value.
        Throws:
        DeviceException
